reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I have been looking for! Excellent quality!
reviews.reviewText: I have been using hand towels under my dish drying rack, which isn’t the most attractive look, so I have been looking for the dish rack mat that has it all! This design is modern and has a variety of colors if you want to change it up. The material is flexible, but sturdy! And is very easy to clean either by hand or dish washer! My dish drying rack fits perfectly, and it catches any water that drips down. I would love to get a few more colors of this product to change up the look of my kitchen soon! Amazing!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Multifunction and practical silicone mat
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I really like this mat. It’s flexible which makes it easy to clean between the raised parts, and it’s elevated just enough so that it can hold quite a lot of water while letting your cups and glasses and even dishes drain properly. Since it’s silicone, which I’m a big fan of, you can also use it to place hot items on it That came off the stove or oven. But I use it predominantly as a low profile cup and dish rack when I’m doing a quick wash for a handful of glasses. Really well-made and I expected to last for a really long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great small drying mat for next to sink
reviews.reviewText: I needed a nice colored narrow drying mat for a sink that is adjacent to a corner in my kitchen (I have contend with an odd triangular corner). I was going to get a black mat, but this chocolate brown mat is beautiful and functional. Excellent quality, can through in dishwasher to wash it out if needed. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Pros: love the size - it's perfect for my space! I purchased the clear one to blend into my counter top. The material is great and I love the design.Con: I shake off dishes, etc. that I wash and rinse and then put onto the mat. The little bit of water that collects in the grooves doesn't dry up. I can leave a few dishes in it for two days and that little bit of water will still be there. So it holds the water rather than a cloth dish mat that would absorb the water.

reviews.reviewText: The whole point of getting this for me was to dry some small kitchen items. It works nicely for the most part except for the fact that after every use I find myself drying all the water underneath the mat. the water seems to go right through.
